{
  "texts": [
    "Recent advancements in artificial intelligence have significantly enhanced olfactory analysis, providing powerful tools to decode complex sensory information.",
    "By leveraging techniques such as machine learning and data mining, researchers have gained deeper insights into the mechanisms underlying odor perception and their practical implications.",
    "The current focus of AI in olfactory research spans several key areas, which will be elaborated upon in the following sections.",
    "Before the integration of AI, olfactory analysis primarily relied on conventional statistical methods and heuristic approaches.",
    "Techniques such as gas chromatography (GC), mass spectrometry (MS), and principal component analysis (PCA) were widely used to profile 1 3 and interpret volatile compounds (Lubes and Goodarzi 2017)."
  ]
}